<subSubSection id="C369656A6C7855201B2AFEBBFC627FC5" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B2AFEBBFDB97F09" blockId="13.[264,561,283,309]" box="[264,561,283,309]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading id="D084818D6C7855201B2AFEBBFDB97F09" bold="true" box="[264,561,283,309]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201B2AFEBBFDB97F09" authority="Fry, 1978" authorityName="Fry" authorityYear="1978" box="[264,561,283,309]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Pallenopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C7855201B2AFEBBFDB97F09" bold="true" box="[264,561,283,309]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Pallenopsidae Fry, 
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201BD4FEBBFDB97F09" box="[502,561,283,309]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B2AFEC7FC627FC5" blockId="13.[264,1325,359,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
There has been an erratic history of the familial attribution of species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201EC1FEC7FE737F95" authority="Wilson, 1881" authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="1881" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" genus="Pallenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C7855201EC1FEC7FEDB7F94" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pallenopsis</emphasis>
Wilson, 
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201B9FFE2FFE737F95" box="[445,507,399,425]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1881.0">1881</number>
</taxonomicName>
. For many years it was placed within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C78552019C5FE2FFB147F95" box="[999,1180,399,425]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Callipallenidae</taxonomicName>
, with which it was consistent in having, 
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C785520187AFE17FD4D7FEC" box="[600,709,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">inter alia</emphasis>
, a 
<number id="3DBB24C66C78552018CFFE17FC807FED" box="[749,776,439,465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="10.0">10</number>
­articled oviger in both sexes, palps absent or present only as small, one­articled buds, and functional chelae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C369656A6C7855201B1AFDA7FBC47B25" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B1AFDA7FD147CA5" blockId="13.[264,1325,359,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201B1AFDA7FE5B7C1D" author="Stock" box="[312,467,519,545]" pageId="13" pageNumber="27" refString="Stock, J. H. (1978) Abyssal Pycnogonida from the North-eastern Atlantic Basin, Part I. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 19, 189 - 219." type="journal article" year="1978">
Stock (
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201BAFFDA7FE427C1D" box="[397,458,519,545]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
transferred the genus to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201913FDA7FC7C7C1D" box="[817,1012,519,545]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phoxichilidiidae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201E15FDA7FEDF7C75" author="Arnaud" pageId="13" pageNumber="25" refString="Arnaud, F. &amp; Bamber, R. N. (1987) The Biology of Pycnogonida. Advances in Marine Biology, 24, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1987">
Arnaud and Bamber (
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201B33FD8FFEC67C75" box="[273,334,559,585]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
followed his example. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201844FD8FFD7D7C75" author="Child" box="[614,757,559,585]" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" refString="Child, C. A. (1992) Shallow-water Pycnogonida of the Gulf of Mexico. Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises, 9 (1), 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="1992">
Child (
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201894FD8FFD7D7C75" box="[694,757,559,585]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201923FD8FFCB57C75" author="Child" box="[769,829,559,585]" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" refString="Child, C. A. (1995) Antarctic and Subantarctic Pycnogonida: V, The families Pycnogonidae, Phoxichilidiidae, Endeididae and Callipallenidae, including the Genus Pallenopsis. Biology of the Antarctic Seas XXIV (Ed. S. D. Cairns). American Geophysical Union, Antarctic Research Series, 69, 113 - 165." type="journal article" year="1995">
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201923FD8FFCB57C75" box="[769,829,559,585]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) returned the genus to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201E50FD8FFAAE7C75" box="[1138,1318,559,585]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Callipallenidae</taxonomicName>
, an opinion supported by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201814FDF7FD707C4D" author="Bamber" box="[566,760,599,625]" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" refString="Bamber, R. N. (2002 a) Morphological variation in and a redescription of Pallenopsis (Bathypallenopsis) tritonis Hoek, 1883 (Arthropoda: Pycnogonida). Journal of Natural History, 36, 157 - 172." type="journal article" year="2002" yearSuffix="a">
Bamber (
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201884FDF7FD6C7C4D" box="[678,740,599,625]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2002.0">2002</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
as the protonymphon larva was not consistent with those of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201BF1FDDFFD1F7CA5" box="[467,663,639,665]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phoxichilidiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B1AFD07FCD27D2D" blockId="13.[264,1325,359,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
All of these opinions were attempting to fit the genus into one of the existing families of the Pycnogonida, despite the fact that at least two of those were generally accepted as being polyphyletic (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201804FD57FCC57D2D" author="Arnaud" box="[550,845,759,785]" pageId="13" pageNumber="25" refString="Arnaud, F. &amp; Bamber, R. N. (1987) The Biology of Pycnogonida. Advances in Marine Biology, 24, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1987">
Arnaud &amp; Bamber, 
<number id="3DBB24C66C785520192CFD57FCC57D2D" box="[782,845,759,785]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B1AFCBFFC8C7A15" blockId="13.[264,1325,359,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
In his multivariate analyses, Fry (
<number id="3DBB24C66C78552018E6FCBFFC897D05" box="[708,769,799,825]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1978.0">1978</number>
) found 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C785520197FFCBFFC6E7D04" box="[861,998,799,824]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" genus="Pallenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C785520197FFCBFFC6E7D04" box="[861,998,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pallenopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be isolated near (but not very close to) 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201B93FCE7FDEF7D5C" box="[433,615,839,864]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" genus="Anoplodactylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C7855201B93FCE7FDEF7D5C" box="[433,615,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Anoplodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201883FCE7FCC07D5C" box="[673,840,839,864]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Ammotheidae" genus="Prototrygaeus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C7855201883FCE7FCC07D5C" box="[673,840,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Prototrygaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He therefore proposed the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201EC4FCE7FEFB7DB5" class="Pycnogonida" family="Pallenopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pallenopsidae</taxonomicName>
, within the suborder Pallenopsida. Although Fry maintained that the results of this analysis were only a &quot;primary hypothesis of degrees of overall morphological similarities&quot;, when judged against the continuing controversy over the placement of this genus in relation to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201B98FC47FDE37A3D" box="[442,619,999,1025]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Callipallenidae</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C78552018F5FC47FC1F7A3D" box="[727,919,999,1025]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phoxichilidiidae</taxonomicName>
they reinforce the concept of the distinction of this genus at the family level.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B1AFB97FB667A45" blockId="13.[264,1325,359,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Recent cladistic analyses of the Pycnogonida (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201940FB97FB8B7A6D" author="Arango" box="[866,1027,1079,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="25" refString="Arango, C. P. (2002) Morphological phylogenetics of the sea spiders (Arthropoda: Pycnogonida). Organisms, Diversity &amp; Evolution, 2, 107 - 125." type="journal article" year="2002">
Arango 
<number id="3DBB24C66C78552019E7FB97FB8B7A6D" box="[965,1027,1079,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24B106C7855201E32FB97FBC47A6D" author="Arango" box="[1040,1100,1079,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="25" refString="Arango, C. P. (2003) Molecular approach to the phylogenetics of sea spiders (Arthropoda, Pycnogonida) using partial sequences of nuclear ribosomal DNA. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 28, 588 - 600." type="journal article" year="2003">
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201E32FB97FBC47A6D" box="[1040,1100,1079,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) indicated that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201B76FBFFFE557A44" box="[340,477,1119,1144]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" genus="Pallenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C7855201B76FBFFFE557A44" box="[340,477,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pallenopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
related poorly to either the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201900FBFFFC6A7A45" box="[802,994,1119,1145]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phoxichilidiidae</taxonomicName>
or the 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201E16FBFFFB617A45" box="[1076,1257,1119,1145]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Callipallenidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC36E16C7855201B1AFB27FBC47B25" blockId="13.[264,1325,359,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
It now seems appropriate to take the logical conclusion from these various clues, and recognize the genus as inappropriate to either of these families; rather, the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C7855201EC4FB0FFEF87ACD" class="Pycnogonida" family="Pallenopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pallenopsidae</taxonomicName>
of Fry (
<number id="3DBB24C66C7855201BECFB77FD837ACD" box="[462,523,1239,1265]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1978.0">1978</number>
) is re­erected for 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D626C78552018FBFB77FCEA7ACC" box="[729,866,1239,1264]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Phoxichilidiidae" genus="Pallenopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EAF36C78552018FBFB77FCEA7ACC" box="[729,866,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pallenopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It may further prove appropriate (or at least convenient) to raise Stock’s (
<number id="3DBB24C66C78552018BBFB5FFD5E7B25" box="[665,726,1279,1305]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1974.0">1974</number>
) subgenera to full generic rank.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
